.TH "af_alg_wait_for_data" 9 "af_alg_wait_for_data" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
af_alg_wait_for_data \- wait for availability of TX data
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" af_alg_wait_for_data
.BI "(struct sock *sk "  ","
.BI "unsigned flags "  ","
.BI "unsigned min "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sk" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "flags" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "min" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

\fIsk\fP socket of connection to user space
\fIflags\fP If MSG_DONTWAIT is set, then only report if function would sleep
\fImin\fP Set to minimum request size if partial requests are allowed.
\fIreturn\fP 0 when writable memory is available, < 0 upon error
